title: High school football rankings for Oct. 20, 2015
text:
By Greg Joyce | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 20, 2015 10:00 AM View/Post Comments 
Things are getting messy, and they're only about to get even messier. 
The top three remain the same and the bottom three remain the same. In between is where it's tough to sort things out. 
Central Catholic was the victim of the upset of the weekend, losing to Emmaus. That knocks the Vikings from their No. 4 spot. Nazareth bounced back with a big win while Easton dropped another game to Parkland . Meanwhile, Saucon Valley kept on winning big -- as did the teams below them, but the Panthers have been knocking on the door to move up all year and this was their week to do it. 
And with Weeks 8, 9 and 10 bringing more matchups between Top 5 teams, we're only getting started with the mayhem.
